LUSAKA, Dec. 22 (Xinhua) -- Cases of the coronavirus in Zambia continued surging as 2,857 new cases were registered over the past 24 hours, the highest since the fourth wave of the pandemic started, the country's health ministry said on Wednesday. The health ministry said the new cases were found from 12,380 tests done during the period, representing a 23 percent positivity. This brings the cumulative cases to 221,880. A total of 148 patients were discharged, bringing the total recoveries to 207,709 while no deaths were recorded with the total deaths still standing at 3,685. On Monday, the health ministry officially announced that the country had entered into the fourth wave of the pandemic, with the majority of the cases being infections with the Omicron variant.  Enditem